  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Autoimmune thrombocytopenic purpura is an immunological disorder characterized by increased
      platelet destruction due to presence of anti-platelet antibodies. Hepatitis C virus
      infection, which is one of the most common chronic viral infections worldwide, may cause
      secondary chronic immune thrombocytopenic purpura. It seemed to play a pathogenic role in
      autoimmune thrombocytopenic purpura. Moreover, the successful response (negative hepatitis C
      virus - ribonucleic acid) to tapered steroids and antiviral therapy was useful to revert
      thrombocytopenia
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
